    "reasoning": "To implement the Lemmings game behavior described, we need a Moore state machine with two states: walking left and walking right. The state transitions depend on the bump_left and bump_right inputs. When a bump occurs (either on left or right or both), the Lemming changes direction. We'll use areset to asynchronously reset the machine to walk left. Since this is a Moore machine, outputs depend only on the current state. The implementation will use two states (logic values 0 and 1) to represent walk_left and walk_right. We'll use a synchronous reset with areset asserting high to reset the state to walk left. In the state transition logic, we check the bump conditions to determine if a flip in direction is needed. The output logic reflects the current state. We ensure all signals are declared as logic, and use always @(*) for combinational logic.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input areset,\n    input bump_left,\n    input bump_right,\n    output walk_left,\n    output walk_right\n);\n\n    // Define states\n    localparam WALK_LEFT = 1'b0;\n    localparam WALK_RIGHT = 1'b1;\n\n    // State register\n    logic current_state;\n    logic next_state;\n\n    // Sequential logic for state register\n    always @(posedge clk or posedge areset) begin\n        if (areset)\n            current_state <= WALK_LEFT;\n        else\n            current_state <= next_state;\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic for next state\n    always @(*) begin\n        if (bump_left || bump_right) begin\n            // Change direction based on current state\n            if (current_state == WALK_LEFT)\n                next_state = WALK_RIGHT;\n            else\n                next_state = WALK_LEFT;\n        end else begin\n            // No change in direction\n            next_state = current_state;\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Output logic for walk_left and walk_right\n    always @(*) begin\n        if (current_state == WALK_LEFT)\n            {walk_left, walk_right} = 2'b10;\n        else\n            {walk_left, walk_right} = 2'b01;\n    end\n\nendmodule"
